Written evidence from the National Federation of Retail Newsagents [TOB07]
defaultIntroductiondefault1. 
defaultThe National Federation of Retail Newsagents (NFRN) would like to thank the Committee for the invitation to make a written submission on the issue of tobacco smuggling.
default2. The NFRN is one of Europe’s largest trade associations, representing over 
default16,000
default 
defaultfee paying members from approximately 
default18
default,000 
defaultindependent newsagents and convenience stores across the UK, Channel Islands and the Republic of Ireland.
default 
defaultWe are a membership led organisation
default 
defaultthat 
defaultis
default democratically structured
default;
default 
defaultpolicy is made by annual conference and its implementation is overseen by National Council.
default3. 
defaultThe NFRN assist
defaults
default the independent retailer to  compete more effectively in today’s highly competitive market through the provision of practical help and assistance, commercial support, deals and buying opportunities, training, expertise and services, it also represents its members’ interests at gover
defaultnmental and parliamentary level
default, as well as within the news and magazine industry
